Package: pi-usb-safegate
Version: 1.0.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Essential: no
Depends: python3 (>= 3.7), python3-pip, python3-tk, python3-dev, clamav, clamav-daemon, clamav-freshclam, udev, mount, util-linux, curl, wget, gksu
Recommends: desktop-file-utils, shared-mime-info
Suggests: systemd
Installed-Size: 1024
Maintainer: PI USB Data Safegate Team <noreply@example.com>
Description: Secure USB to cloud transfer with malware scanning
 PI USB Data Safegate is a security-focused application for Raspberry Pi
 that provides secure transfer of files from USB drives to cloud storage.
 .
 Key features:
  - Malware scanning using ClamAV before upload
  - Support for Nextcloud and Dropbox cloud storage
  - Email notifications with download links
  - Automatic cleanup after 7 days
  - User-friendly GUI interface
  - Real-time status updates
 .
 This application is designed for Raspberry Pi OS and other Debian-based
 systems. It requires root privileges to access USB devices securely.
Homepage: https://github.com/example/pi-usb-safegate
Bugs: https://github.com/example/pi-usb-safegate/issues